                              reviewerName: "Emilia Nieminen",
                              reviewText:
                                   "Main destination in Hanoi!\n\nInteresting museum, especially garment history and architecture in mind. I loved being able to go into old stilt houses and studying the construction techniques.\n\nFew words of criticism:\n\nSignage is not very clear. I could not find a toilet in the new building and there was no one at the information desk. Had to use the restaurant toilet. WC signs are the most crucial part of a public building.\n\nLighting is poorly designed. The pieces could benefit from darker rooms with spots inside the cases. Often the TV monitors and lights are reflected in the glass and it's hard to see the objects.\n\nDo not miss the museum grounds! There are many wonderful old buildings there. Also note that the grounds have two museums. I thought there was just the old one and nearly missed the modern one entirely.\n\nGift shop:\nIt breaks my heart that they dismantle old museum quality native garments to make souvenirs like plush toys. Someone spent months lovingly hand embroidering and batique dying a piece of cloth that is now treated like rubbish. Sad fate to valuable old pieces of history.",
