                              reviewerName: "Jessica Nubla",
                              reviewText:
                                   "The Temple of Literature is a must-see for all students. Experience the dedication and the spirit of Vietnamese people in learning and education.\n\nIt is a common practice in Hanoi for graduating students to visit the Temple and offer their prayers.\n\nThe place offers an audio guide, however, the headphones provided do not cover the ear and cannot block outside noise, so I couldn't hear much of the guide. 😞 But from what I could hear, Vietnam has a rich history in Confucionism. They honored their scholars, and every part of the temple teaches the basic principles of education and the discipline required for it.\n\nIt was a very soulful experience, despite the failure of the audio guide to reduce outside noise.\n\nThe souvenir shop beside the exit also has products made by local Vietnamese artists, so be sure to visit it. :)",
                              rating: 5,
                              rank: 7,
