                              reviewText:
                                   "Took us a few hours to wander around this museum. There are two separate buildings and one is for the ancient Vietnam exhibits (which is pretty impressive) and the other is for post-1945 Vietnam (French revolution, etc).\n\nThey have a vast collection of pre-historic artifacts dating back to the Stone Age; it’s obvious that Vietnam has excellent archeological efforts.\n\nThese are really old buildings built during the French rule so it’s a bit creepy walking around dark corridors and spaces, and some areas aren’t well-ventilated, although I think it adds to the experience while looking at ancient mystic objects, i felt like it added to the thrill..:)\n\nOverall, a must-visit if you like history and art. And who doesn’t? 🙃",
