                              reviewText:
                                   "Recommend checking if it’s a special day before going… we didn’t and ended up visiting on Uncle Ho’s 130th birthday😂 It was incredible, even if it was a total coincidence, we went there with half of Hanoi it felt like. The que system was exceptionally organized.\n\nRecommend covering Shoulders and knees if you are to visit the main man himself. If not you’ll get rejected before security. At the check they take any liquids, you get a blue bag with you deliver, get a note and pick up at exit. Also no camera equipment allowed, you a get a red bag for the camera and do the same, just a little later down the line.\n\nWhen you get close to the end you’ll get yelled at if you use the phone, and they are pretty strict on no phones.\n\nInside the mausoleum was incredible. Just have to experience it, we felt it well worth the visit, ecpesially on his birthday 19. May\n\nHad to buy cover ups for our knees, but other than that is was free entry to the mausoleum, afterwords it’s 40k entry per person to see the presidential palace and such",
