                              reviewerName: "Happy Bird",
                              reviewText:
                                   "We stumbled on Sofitel Legend Metropole Hanoi while exploring the city and were curious to see what it was like inside. The hotel is one of the most famous and prestigious in Hanoi and it has a rich history.\n\nAs we walked into the hotel, it felt like we were transported back to another era. The hotel has a classic French colonial style, with white walls, green shutters and red tiled roof. The lobby was spacious and elegant with marble floors, chandeliers and antique furniture. Even through we were not hotel guests, the staff were very polite and welcoming. We continued to wander around the hotel to see what it had to offer and were amazed by the variety and quality of the facilities and services. The hotel has a beautiful garden, an outdoor pool, a spa and fitness center and a boutique.  One of the highlights of the hotel has to be its gastronomy. The hotel has several restaurants and bars, each with its own theme and cuisine.\n\nWe had a great time wandering through Sofitel Legend Metropole Hanoi. The hotel is more than just a place to stay, it is a destination itself, one that we may one day stay at as hotel guests ourselves. It combines the charm and elegance of the past with the comfort and convenience of the present. It is a perfect example of Hanoi's culture, history, and luxury.",
