                              reviewText:
                                   "During my recent 9-night sojourn at the Sofitel Legend Metropole Hanoi, I was struck by the grandeur and history of the hotel making this an unforgettable stay. The hotel is an architectural masterpiece, that stands as a beacon of French elegance and Vietnamese culture.  My wife was on a medical mission in Hanoi and I was left alone at the Metropole working remotely.  The Metropole became my sanctuary - I could have stayed here forever.\n\nThe hotel is a Grand Hotel but it's just right - not too big but big enough to have everything you want. Great spa, five fantastic restaurants, a gym, a pool and so many quiet spots to sit and read or work.  You feel the spirits of all the luminaries that have stayed here - Charlie Chaplin, Somerset Maugham, and Graham Greene are a few. And you sense the pivotal moments of history that have occurred (and still occur) at this hotel - it has a profound sense of place.\n\nThe staff cherishes the Hotel's history and prominence and they provide a sense of warm caring hospitality that is unmatched.  Attentive, professional, and friendly but again dignified and reserved - in no way overbearing.  I will go back next year and look forward to staying at the Metropole - so many great stories that I want to make this hotel a part of my story.",
