                                   "It is said to be the birth of egg coffee, with a recipe founded way back in 1940s. Located in old quarters, it is easily accessible yet also easy to miss while walking along the main road due to its narrow entrance.\n\nAfter walking through a short alleyway, you will be greeted by the staff who speak very good English. There are 2 levels in this cafe, do sit at level 2 balcony area for some street view. Menu includes coffee, tea, as well as juices, but if you’re here, do order the famous egg coffee. As strange as it may sound, it has a long history where egg yolk was used to replace the scarce milk, and has now become a well know Hanoian delicacy.\n\nHot egg coffee will be served with a small thermal bath to keep it warm. Start off by scooping up a little of the foam to taste it, it’s foamy and rich and has a slight hint of egg in that. Then, you may try some of the coffee beneath it. After that how you consume it is totally up to you (do note that the coffee can be quite hot so be careful). I definitely enjoyed the hot egg coffee more, especially in the cooler winter weather.\n\nOverall, a definite must to visit this place - for the coffee, for the history, for the ambiance.",
