                              time: "2022-08-12T04:03:23.000Z",
                              reviewerName: "Phuong L",
                              reviewText:
                                   "It locates some 14 km from city centre of Hanoi. In a hot summer day & in adventure mood, we took local city bus number 47A departing from LONG BIÊN station. Its last stop is BÁT TRÀNG ceramic village's market. City Bus is a very basic means of transport. It costs only 7000 VND/ one way ( $ AUD 0,5), taking 30 mins. Don't take 47A bus line if you can afford to rent a private car ( especially you may buy something heavy & don't want to carry all along).\n\nThis village's market operates in traditional way meaning lots of bargain, no air conditioning, narrow pathway, selling mix of genuine village products as well as imported ones. Try to avoid its public toilet if you can. Otherwise, I enjoyed good fun of watching local artists working in workshop. Outside market, there're many townhouse shops selling up market items. There are tourist electrical cars serving visitors if you can not walk long.\n\nTIPs: For whom like something cool drinks or clean restroom, just 800m away from market, you look for ECOPARK \" residential village\". There you enjoy drinks comfortably in air conditioned space in Highlands Coffee or, Starbucks Coffee.  Near exit ( entrance) to Ecopark, you will notify a Bus Stop Sign so no need to return the village market. Just wait here to catch the same 47A city bus. There's a ticket conductor working on bus, you pay cash & he gives ticket.",
