                              reviewerName: "Krishnanunni Jeevan",
                              reviewText:
                                   "The hotel service goes way beyond expectations.The hotel itself is four star but service is above 7 star hotels . I was already scammed by the time I reached hotel from airport but the staff went above and beyond and helped me get my money back. They put a lot of time and effort to do it even though it was my stupidity to not to listen to their welcome email and take a fake grab from airport. Each member of the staff Linda , Saffron, Chloe, Lilly, Macus, Leon and the cleaning ladies , tries so hard to make your stay worthwhile. I think if you follow the standard , it is easy to provide a nice hotel stay but to make a hotel feel like home , it is very hard. I have to say this guys have succeeded in that . I initially booked only for 3 nights but since it was an amazing service I extended 3 more nights. Linda helped me with tours and gave me good suggestions. I personally think it is better to book from hotel since she makes sure you get what you want and deals with any unexpected changes. I saw that she was working so hard to reschedule tours for some customers because of unexpected typhoon. The breakfast is also amazing. They do cleaning everyday, I got a deluxe room , was quite big for a single person but I like the space. The ceiling is quite high, feels like you are in a palace. There is also a small it functional gym in top floor where I did yoga everyday. The staff also helps with you any silly doubts , gives good suggestions for street food and always happy to talk to you when you are bored . There has been late nights when I was offered free snacks and tea while just chatting in the lobby.",
