                              reviewerName: "Andrea Wolfe",
                              reviewText:
                                   "UNSANITARY. BED BUGS & MOLD\nI have no idea how this place has so many good reviews, My experience was absolutely terrible.\nUpon entering the room it seemed very run down; but we aren’t picky and don’t mind staying in an older hotel. We dropped our bags and left to explore.\nWe came back late, and to our surprise the staff was downstairs sleeping on the couch-this spooked us because it was pitch black and we weren’t expecting someone to be sleeping in the lobby.\n\nWhen we got to the room I turned on the shower and accidentally (but thankfully) hit the button to the bathtub jets-The jets turned on and started shooting black fluffy mold out into the bathtub. These jets had obviously never been cleaned before. I went to go tell my husband and was informed that the night has gotten worse- he found a bed bug. He was looking at the sheets , because they were stained , and he noticed the bug by the head board.\n\nWe tore the bed apart  looking in the sheets and in/under the mattress with flashlights (because the one lamp next to the bed didn’t work-surprise) only to find multiple bed bugs in the mattress.\nAlong with little bugs we also found piles of hair under the mattress cover (that was not mine as we hadn’t even laid in the bed yet) and hair and dust in the head board making it clear they don’t clean these rooms.\n\nWe told the staff (who was downstairs sleeping in the lobby) and they told us they had no more rooms but changed our sheets (with similar yellow stained sheets). The staff at the hotel was very sweet and as helpful as they could be , but we didn’t feel comfortable staying in the room for the rest of our stay, so we booked another hotel and left that next morning.\n\nWhen we contacted the manager , Linda, she refused to give us a refund. We paid for 4 nights and had to leave because the room was so unsanitary and they didn’t have another room for us. We showed her pictures and videos and she still refused to give us a refund; but instead she tried to flip the situation and blame us because we had left and didn’t fulfill our 4 nights. She thought that changing the sheets was enough, but the room needs a total deep clean and the mattress needs to be discarded.\n\nI understand stuff happens when you’re traveling abroad and you’re bound to run into a situation like this at some point. I just think the way Linda handled it was unprofessional and it was very upsetting that we have to pay for a hotel that we didn’t stay in for a reason the hotel was responsible for. We had been traveling around Asia for a month and stayed in many different hotels, and this was by far the worst experience we have ever had.",
