                              reviewText:
                                   "Location, Location, Location. This is the mantra of real estate and Luxury old quarter has taken this advice well. It’s situated very close to Hoan Kiem lake, where you can go out for your morning walks or evening strolls. It’s also close by to the Hang Dao street where Night Market gets setup on FRI-SUN from 06:00 PM - 12:00 AM. This is the best place to do shopping in Hanoi. Put on your haggling hats and catch those lucrative deals. In addition, there are a lot of good restaurants in nearby roads including Bun Cha Dac Kim a Michelin rated eatery.\n\nWe got a family suite which had excellent city views. The rooms were clean and hygienic. The hotel staff were very friendly and helpful. The breakfast is served on the first floor and is freshly prepared on request.\n\nWe took help of Lynda (the manager) to book trips to Ha Long Bay, Pottery village and Sapa for us. She did an excellent job understanding our requirements and our trip schedule so that she can connect us to the right points in the trip and ensured we reached back to Hanoi airport from Sapa safely.\n\nThanks a lot to the Luxury old quarter team for making our trip so memorable.",
